{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> φᾰλακρ-ός</b>, ά, όν, <br /> (φαλός, ἄκρος) <b>baldheaded,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Anacreon Lyricus 68, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.12, 4.23, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἀφορισμοί” 6.34, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 495e, “Sammelb.” 4637.16 (2nd c.BC)\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>], etc.; properly <b>bald on the crown,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 518a27; φ. τὴν κεφαλήν 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Luct.” 16; πρόσωπον φαλακρόν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 227; οἱ φαλακροί 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 540 (Lyric poetry), “Pax” 767 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], etc.: proverbial of labour in vain, φαλακρῷ κτένας δανείζειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Prov.” 26; φαλακρὸν τίλλειν 10th c.AD: Suidas Legal icographus \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>like a bald head, blunt, knobbed,</b> φ. σιδήρια of cauterizing irons, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 11; στρογγύλωσις [prev. work] 61 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; φαλακρότερος (variant{-ώτερος}) εὐδίας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophron Comicus 108. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>bald spot,</b> ἔχειν φαλακρόν τινα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Anonymus “Incred.” 17. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> ὁ φ. name of a fallacy, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 2.108. [φᾰλᾰκρός E.[same place], 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 540.] \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9615","accentedUnicode":"φαλακρός","shortDef":"bald","mediumDef":"bald","stepGloss":"bald","stepTransliteration":"falakros","_step_Type":"word"}]}